Step 1. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities are represented by the Total Current Liabilities = 3,389,719.66, and Total Owner’s Equity is 16,111,731.83.  
• Debt to Equity = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity = 3,389,719.66 / 16,111,731.83 ≈ 0.2103  
• Rounded, this is 0.21  

Step 2. Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit is 111,731.83 and Total Revenue is 791,992.51.  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (111,731.83 / 791,992.51) × 100 ≈ 14.11%  

Step 3. Return on Assets (ROA)  
• The Total Assets at period-end is 19,501,451.49.  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100 = (111,731.83 / 19,501,451.49) × 100 ≈ 0.573%  
• Rounded, this is 0.57%  

Step 4. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Turnover is typically calculated as Total Revenue divided by the Average Accounts Receivable.  
• The beginning Accounts Receivable is 0.00 and ending is 248,540.09.  
• Average Accounts Receivable = (0.00 + 248,540.09) / 2 = 124,270.045  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable = 791,992.51 / 124,270.045 ≈ 6.38  

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.21",
    "Net Profit Margin": "14.11%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "0.57%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "6.38"
  }
}
